theorem Topology.P2_of_dense_interiorClosure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X)) : Topology.P2 A := by
  -- First, deduce that `closure A = univ`.
  have hClosure_eq_univ : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact Set.Subset_univ _
    · intro x _
      have hx_int : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
        have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
          trivial
        simpa [h] using this
      exact (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X)) hx_int
  -- Hence `closure A` is open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    simpa [hClosure_eq_univ] using isOpen_univ
  -- Apply the auxiliary lemma for open closures.
  exact Topology.P2_of_open_closure (A := A) hOpen
